00:49:32,236 --> 00:49:35,015
No, he is deformed!

400
00:49:36,116 --> 00:49:40,274
A freak!
He looks like a squashed octopus!

401
00:49:42,396 --> 00:49:46,791
Our mother died giving birth to us.
He was attached to my right side.

402
00:49:46,792 --> 00:49:50,436
They wouldn't let us go to school
or anything.  They kept us hidden.

403
00:49:50,437 --> 00:49:56,035
We were the big family secret.
Everyone hated us, except our aunt.

404
00:49:56,176 --> 00:49:58,142
Listen, he likes the dark,

405
00:49:58,143 --> 00:50:01,530
he doesn't like to be seen,
not even by me, sometimes.

406
00:50:01,534 --> 00:50:02,646
And you know what else?

407
00:50:02,677 --> 00:50:05,405
He talks to me, up
here, without words.

408
00:50:05,415 --> 00:50:07,328
I just hear him
whispering in my brain.

409
00:50:07,329 --> 00:50:10,109
Sometimes he talks for
hours, he won't shut up!

410
00:50:10,116 --> 00:50:12,437
I used to be able to
talk to him like that,

411
00:50:12,438 --> 00:50:14,717
but that's when we
were still connected.

412
00:50:14,752 --> 00:50:17,384
Our aunt said it
was our special gift,

413
00:50:17,385 --> 00:50:20,396
but since we have been
separated, I can't do it anymore.

414
00:50:20,397 --> 00:50:24,524
But he can still do it to me,
in fact, he's even better at it now.

415
00:50:24,525 --> 00:50:28,472
